name: Lei's Asian Bistro
text: order takeout from them for the first time . it was awesome . the food is great . the people are extremely helpful and friendly . the selection was huge . i give this place a 10 out of 10 . this will definitely be one of my go to spots .

name: The Lox
text: fun , tasty but little seating . best for takeout , but worth it ! unusual options along with traditional bagels and cream cheese .

name: Raising Cane's Chicken Fingers
text: my columbus friends have been talking this joint up to me for months now . they were completely flabbergasted that in my time at osu as an undergrad student i had never eaten here . oops ? anyway , so there was a lot of build up . sometimes , build up can be the worst because you go in expecting the best and things have to be 100 magical in order for there to be 0 disappointment . thankfully , this experience wasn t exactly a disappointment , but i did feel mildly let down . i know i will get crap for this from my friends , but i have a confession i like chick fil a s chicken better . in the words of my man friend golden fried bigotry never tasted so good . that being said , i did genuinely appreciate the sweet tea and sides . i also was not as impressed with the toast as my friends thought i should be . it wasn t bad , it just wasn t as amazing as everyone else seemed to think it was , but maybe i m just strange seeing as how i m the only one who felt this way in a group of seven . oh yeah , and the sauce . for you northern californians , it reminds me of a less spicy version of la vic s sauce . i do wish they had a cane s a little closer , as i d definitely prefer it over kfc but seeing as how the last time i ate at kfc was probably about 10 years ago , it s not really a biggie . hopefully i don t get disowned for this review .

name: The Refectory Restaurant
text: this is by far one of the best food experiences that i have had in all my travel . i think this is where food and science pair so well to provide such an amazing and savory experience to your palate ! ! if you are new to these food experiences please take a look at my pictures below and just imagine the quality that this place provides . the refectory is definitely in a class of there own . thanks again for an amazing experience ! i left happy my wife did and my palate too . . .

name: Union Cafe
text: ugh . i try so hard to like this place but then someone from their staff is just rude . went with a couple of friends and a guy who works there got in front of my friends and i in line . i was confused so i just nicely said that we had been there for a little and he looked at us like we were beneath him and he was just mean and said he works there so he doesn t stand in lines and they all went ahead . it was fine that he went ahead but his attitude was unnecessary and mean for no reason . we have to remember that all lgbt have to be nice to each other regardless of the day you are having . it s important so we are always there with open arms for the many who are finally finding strength from our bars , clubs and restaurants .
